In one case, it concerns, for example, disabled people, in another, personal problems or health problems of employees.
Among the 14 finalists from across the Republic was the Prague software company Et Netera, which supports the formation of informal sports teams among its employees, who then participate in tournaments in various sports.
Another example of a company responsible for the Pardubice area is the company Isolit-Bravo, which has been the main funder of disabled children for seven years.
In Poděbrad, there is a stationery shop which is particularly concerned about the health problems of its workers, who make up more than 70% of the workforce; this is why it was awarded the title of the company responsible for the central area of the Czech Republic and in the Vodafone Company of the Year competition it finished in third place in the region.
In Olomouc won the accounting firm MiRyz Soft, which reduced working hours, even below the average of 35 hours per week, without reducing wages.
