'If the representatives of the competing undertakings did not answer the questions, they could not take part in the contest for Responsible Business of the Year, but they are not disqualified from the main contest for Vodafone Business of the Year.'
"Individual applications for this competition are not allowed, as it is a subcategory of the main Enterprise of the Year competition", explains Karel Goldman of the consultancy firm Bison & Rose.
Police made arrests during a public auction at the Agricultural Fund building in Pilsen
The anti-corruption police made several arrests at the Agricultural Fund building in recent days.
Detectives handcuffed a local media entrepreneur and real estate developer Luboš G.
This appears to have been an attempt to manipulate an ongoing public auction for the restitution of the rights so that the auctioned land would be received by a specific interested party.
He owed Luboš G. half a million crowns for it.
"At the moment I can only say that the police are looking for a person for bribery during a public auction and public tender", the head of the general prosecutor of Pilsen Antonie Zelená told Právo, adding that at the moment she cannot divulge more details about the ongoing investigation.
After 24 hours, the police released the 46-year-old businessman.
How it could have influenced the public auction, given the lack of official information, can only be speculated.
The spokeswoman of the Agricultural Fund Lubomíra Černá answered Právo's questions saying that the police actually carried out the arrest at the Pilsen headquarters and it was during a public auction.
"This is a customer, not one of our workers", he said.
According to Černá, the public auction is called 'Call for Proposals for Land Transfer in accordance with the Land Law' and is held when several interested parties appear in relation to the offered land.
"These people, during the call, offer a higher value than their restitution, which must be transferred before the land value is announced".
"Based on the bids, the order of buyers is determined and then the Agricultural Fund transfers the land to the person who offers the highest bid", explained the Fund spokeswoman.
Luboš G. had information on who was going to be present at the call and, as he is also an interested party because he acquired various restitution rights, he proposed to the interested parties on the ground that he would not participate in the auction.
