The discovery could prove the theory that creatures exist alongside us and in hostile environments that were thought to be uninhabitable, and it would put on the table the possibility that they could become intelligent beings like us if the conditions in which they live were improved.
Apparently, it is a microbe that was found at the bottom of the Monkey Lake in Yosemite National Park, California, where it lives in an environment that was thought to be too poisonous for any life form, since the lake is rich in arsenic.
Somehow, the creature uses arsenic as a way of survival and this ability raises the possibility that similar life could exist on other planets, which do not have our benevolent atmosphere.
