A 10-year-old child ingests 81 different chemicals in one day, according to a study published Wednesday by the association Generaciones Futuras (the old movement for the rights and respect of future generations).
The association, which warns that its results "have no significant statistical value considering the limited number of samples analysed, but are illustrative of the problematic treated", purchased in supermarkets of Oise and Paris between July and September the food that a child of about ten years usually consumes in four meals and a snack a day.
